00:06:57.555 --> 00:07:01.500 align:middle line:10%
>> So at the climax of the film,
the Jack Nicholson's character

00:07:01.500 --> 00:07:04.990 align:middle line:10%
is trying to figure out what
Faye Dunaway is hiding from

00:07:04.990 --> 00:07:05.790 align:middle line:10%
him.

00:07:05.790 --> 00:07:08.280 align:middle line:10%
And all through the film,
she's been very elusive,

00:07:08.280 --> 00:07:11.440 align:middle line:10%
and hiding her identity, and
acting like she's other people,

00:07:11.440 --> 00:07:12.240 align:middle line:10%
and--

00:07:12.240 --> 00:07:15.800 align:middle line:10%
>> Why she won't come out and
say exactly what's going on.

00:07:15.800 --> 00:07:16.800 align:middle line:90%
He can't figure it out--

00:07:16.800 --> 00:07:17.730 align:middle line:90%
>> He can't figure out.

00:07:17.730 --> 00:07:19.438 align:middle line:84%
>> --like why she's
covering for her dad.

00:07:19.438 --> 00:07:21.075 align:middle line:10%
>> I said I want the truth!

00:07:21.075 --> 00:07:23.580 align:middle line:10%
>> And then finally,
he loses it.

00:07:23.580 --> 00:07:25.120 align:middle line:10%
She's pressed into to the wall.

00:07:25.120 --> 00:07:27.440 align:middle line:10%
He's got his nose almost
cut off, trying to go--

00:07:27.440 --> 00:07:28.495 align:middle line:10%
>> [INAUDIBLE] after him.

00:07:28.495 --> 00:07:30.300 align:middle line:10%
>> He's got everybody after him.

00:07:30.300 --> 00:07:32.220 align:middle line:84%
And so he kind of
loses it because he's

00:07:32.220 --> 00:07:35.400 align:middle line:84%
tired of her lying, and he can't
understand why she's lying.

00:07:35.400 --> 00:07:37.540 align:middle line:84%
So he hits her to try to
get the truth out of her.

00:07:37.540 --> 00:07:41.820 align:middle line:84%
And he finds out that
she is protecting

00:07:41.820 --> 00:07:46.470 align:middle line:84%
a young girl who is her
daughter, but also her sister.

00:07:46.470 --> 00:07:50.490 align:middle line:84%
And then we get the
revelation that Mulwray

00:07:50.490 --> 00:07:55.110 align:middle line:84%
is having sex with his
daughter, and that he is not

00:07:55.110 --> 00:07:57.990 align:middle line:84%
just one of the most
corrupt people that's ever

00:07:57.990 --> 00:08:02.380 align:middle line:84%
been involved in the world
of politics in Los Angeles,

00:08:02.380 --> 00:08:05.450 align:middle line:84%
he's also corrupt to the
core in his own life,

00:08:05.450 --> 00:08:06.264 align:middle line:90%
in his own values.

00:08:06.264 --> 00:08:08.430 align:middle line:84%
And I think it's really
important to talk about that

00:08:08.430 --> 00:08:10.500 align:middle line:90%
because I really believe this.

00:08:10.500 --> 00:08:12.600 align:middle line:84%
I really believe
that when you rise up

00:08:12.600 --> 00:08:14.610 align:middle line:84%
into the higher
realms of the elite,

00:08:14.610 --> 00:08:16.320 align:middle line:84%
you begin discovering
that they're

00:08:16.320 --> 00:08:19.080 align:middle line:84%
involved in some things that
are really disconcerting.

00:08:19.080 --> 00:08:24.120 align:middle line:84%
>> And what's really strange is
that this is a constant theme

00:08:24.120 --> 00:08:27.510 align:middle line:84%
in noir film and in
neo-noir is the--

00:08:27.510 --> 00:08:30.960 align:middle line:84%
there's almost always a
grotesque or some extreme level

00:08:30.960 --> 00:08:32.960 align:middle line:84%
of perversion that's going
on amongst the high--

00:08:32.960 --> 00:08:34.918 align:middle line:84%
when you think about the
Humphrey Bogart films,

00:08:34.918 --> 00:08:38.003 align:middle line:84%
there's a constant theme with
the dames and the broads,

00:08:38.003 --> 00:08:39.419 align:middle line:84%
you know-- all
these femme fatales

00:08:39.419 --> 00:08:43.080 align:middle line:84%
that have the dark secret
and their connection

00:08:43.080 --> 00:08:46.620 align:middle line:84%
to some high-level criminality
that oftentimes does evolve.

00:08:46.620 --> 00:08:50.430 align:middle line:84%
Even in older '40s and '50s
versions of these stories--

00:08:50.430 --> 00:08:51.984 align:middle line:84%
pornography and
drug trafficking,

00:08:51.984 --> 00:08:53.400 align:middle line:84%
which they couldn't
actually show,

00:08:53.400 --> 00:08:55.410 align:middle line:84%
but they would hint at
in a lot of those films,

00:08:55.410 --> 00:09:00.190 align:middle line:84%
like Glass Key and Laura
or these famous noir films.

00:09:00.190 --> 00:09:02.970 align:middle line:84%
And so we have a
representation of that here.

00:09:02.970 --> 00:09:07.350 align:middle line:84%
And again, it just echoes
the constant refrain that's

00:09:07.350 --> 00:09:09.720 align:middle line:90%
in the mainstream media now--

00:09:09.720 --> 00:09:13.410 align:middle line:84%
public stories about high-level
degeneracy and perversion

00:09:13.410 --> 00:09:16.950 align:middle line:84%
that involve these kinds of
trafficking, and sexual incest,

00:09:16.950 --> 00:09:18.180 align:middle line:90%
and things like this.

00:09:18.180 --> 00:09:21.690 align:middle line:84%
>> My favorite uncle was
a high-ranking FBI agent,

00:09:21.690 --> 00:09:25.440 align:middle line:84%
and he served with J. Edgar
Hoover and all of that.

00:09:25.440 --> 00:09:28.950 align:middle line:84%
And right before he
died, I asked him

00:09:28.950 --> 00:09:30.840 align:middle line:84%
what his favorite
movie was, because he

00:09:30.840 --> 00:09:33.797 align:middle line:84%
knew a lot about the world,
and he said Chinatown.

00:09:33.797 --> 00:09:35.880 align:middle line:84%
He said Chinatown was a
movie that if you watch it

00:09:35.880 --> 00:09:38.520 align:middle line:84%
over and over, you'll
really begin to understand

00:09:38.520 --> 00:09:40.402 align:middle line:90%
what this reality is all about.

00:09:40.402 --> 00:09:42.360 align:middle line:84%
And of course, at the
time, I wasn't quite sure

00:09:42.360 --> 00:09:43.470 align:middle line:90%
what he was talking about.

00:09:43.470 --> 00:09:44.340 align:middle line:90%
I was young.

00:09:44.340 --> 00:09:45.960 align:middle line:84%
But now, I actually
see it, and I

00:09:45.960 --> 00:09:48.870 align:middle line:84%
can see it with the
recent revelations

00:09:48.870 --> 00:09:51.600 align:middle line:84%
about high-ranking
people in the government

00:09:51.600 --> 00:09:52.830 align:middle line:90%
and what they're up to.

00:09:52.830 --> 00:09:54.940 align:middle line:84%
And I see that it's
always been here.

00:09:54.940 --> 00:09:56.341 align:middle line:90%
It's never gone away.

00:09:56.341 --> 00:09:58.840 align:middle line:84%
And I think that that's what
Robert Towne, the screenwriter,

00:09:58.840 --> 00:10:00.010 align:middle line:90%
is trying to say--

00:10:00.010 --> 00:10:03.240 align:middle line:84%
that this is an ever-present
evil that is here now

00:10:03.240 --> 00:10:06.180 align:middle line:84%
in Hollywood, i.e. in the
'70s, when the film was built,

00:10:06.180 --> 00:10:08.170 align:middle line:84%
